SeriesDescription: Proportions of positions in the public service compared to national distributions (ratio)
Source: Ministry of Economy and Finance of Ecuador Payment Report
FootNote: The register refers to the total number of civil servants in sector 111 "Central Administration" and 112 "Higher Education Institutions". Only posts in "Occupied" status are taken into account. The following are excluded from "employment status": Scholarship holders, rotating interns, retirees, interns, life pensioners, IESS replacements, eventual replacements, without obligation to the IESS. The registers contain the data provided by each institution.

SeriesDescription: Proportions of positions in the public service compared to national distributions (ratio)
Source: Ministry of Economy and Finance of Ecuador Payment Report
FootNote:
This information was obtained from the payment report of the Ministry of Economy and Finance of Ecuador. Within which, there are no ISCO-08 standardized occupational categories, however, in an approximation exercise, the level of occupation will be considered as a simile to report the information.

Likewise, this information will only consider the sectoral levels of education, health, internal affairs (National Police) and administrative, and information that has identified gender (male/female). 

In order for the information to be considered official, it requires a greater process of information capacity, therefore, it is not suggested that it be considered as such.
